import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['US_Gross'], data['Worldwide_Gross'], label='Movies')
    ax.set_xlabel('US_Gross')
    ax.set_ylabel('Worldwide_Gross')
    ax.set_title('Scatter plot of US_Gross and Worldwide_Gross')
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['Production_Budget'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Production Budget')
    plt.axvline(data['Production_Budget'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['Production_Budget'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Production Budget')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Production_Budget?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    data[['Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating', 'IMDB_Rating']].boxplot()
    plt.title("What is the distribution of Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating and IMDB_Rating?", wrap=True)
    ax.set_xticklabels(['Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating', 'IMDB_Rating'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Running_Time_min'])]
    plt.hist(data['Running_Time_min'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7)
    median_running_time = data['Running_Time_min'].median()
    plt.axvline(median_running_time, color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f'Median: {median_running_time:.2f}')
    plt.xlabel('Running Time (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Running_Time_min?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    mpaa_rating_counts = data['MPAA_Rating'].value_counts()
    ax = mpaa_rating_counts.plot(kind='bar', color=['blue', 'orange', 'green', 'red', 'purple', 'brown', 'pink'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of MPAA_Rating?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('MPAA Rating')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.legend(mpaa_rating_counts.index)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
